The paper discusses the use of deep learning for automated medical image analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The specific applications mentioned in the abstract (breast cancer detection, lung cancer detection, and organ segmentation) also suggest that the paper may fall under the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the use of adversarial training and probabilistic graphical models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
